# Blue Nile Diamond Pendant Review {{year}}: Four Prong, Bezel, Halo & Every Setting Ranked

Blue Nile's [14K yellow gold diamond pendant page](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry?ComponentIDs=DiamondEssentials&MetalType=yg&Diamonds=Dia&diamondBasicsLabel=diamond_pendants&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blue_nile_reviews) runs from a $623 Double-Bail solitaire at 30% off to an $8,695 James Allen Milgrain Bezel at full price. The most important thing to understand before you buy: **most items on this page are pendants only — no chain included.** Blue Nile lists them under the `/necklaces/` URL category, which misleads buyers into expecting a complete piece. Read the product title carefully.

With that established: the Four Prong Basket Solitaire dominates this page by reviews — 39 verified buyers at each of three carat weights. Nothing else on this page comes close. If buyer confidence is your signal, that's where this review starts.

---

## What Is a Diamond Pendant vs a Necklace? Why It Matters Here

This is the section most review sites skip. Blue Nile files everything under "necklaces" in their URL and navigation, but the distinction between a pendant and a necklace is important for buyers — especially when deciding what to order.

**A pendant** is the decorative element alone — the diamond setting with a bail (the small loop at the top through which a chain passes). It hangs from a chain, but the chain is separate. When you buy a pendant from Blue Nile, you are buying the pendant only. A chain is not included unless the product title explicitly says "Pendant Necklace."

**A necklace** is the complete piece — pendant attached to a chain of a defined length. When Blue Nile titles something "Bezel Solitaire **Pendant Necklace**," that item includes a chain. When it's just "Bezel Diamond **Pendant**," it does not.

**Why this matters on this page:** The majority of the 14K yellow gold pieces listed here are pendants only. The "East-West Bezel Solitaire **Pendant Necklace**" series and the "James Allen Bezel Solitaire **Pendant Necklace**" series include chains. Everything else — the Four Prong Basket, Double-Bail, Halo, Double Prong, Bezel, Wire Basket, Kite Set, and all cut-specific solitaires — is a pendant only. You will need to buy a chain separately, or use one you already own.

**What chain to pair:** For a 14K yellow gold pendant, Blue Nile sells matching cable, snake, and box chains. Standard pendant chain length is 18 inches for a collarbone drop or 16 inches for a shorter sit. The bail opening on most round-diamond pendants accommodates chains up to 1.5mm; the East-West bezel bails are often slightly wider.

