## Four Prong Basket Solitaire: The Most Reviewed Pendant on This Page

[![Blue Nile Four Prong Basket diamond pendant in 14K yellow gold lifestyle photo](/images/pendant-round-four-prong-yellow-gold-lifestyle.avif)](/images/pendant-round-four-prong-yellow-gold-lifestyle.avif)

The Four Prong Basket is the dominant setting by every buyer-signal metric. All three reviewed carat weights carry **39 verified reviews** — more than any other pendant family on this page combined. At 25% off across the range, the case for it as the starting point for most buyers is straightforward.

The "basket" refers to a four-pronged open setting where the base of the diamond sits in a small cage — four prongs hold the stone from above, and an open basket beneath maximizes light return from below. This is the setting that makes a round brilliant diamond look its best. Yellow gold prongs add warmth to the H-I color grade.

**Why 39 reviews matters:** A pendant is a personal piece — size, setting height, and balance matter in ways photos don't reveal. Thirty-nine reviews per carat weight means enough buyers confirmed the piece performed as expected. At this price point and with this buyer data, the Four Prong Basket earns the recommendation first.

