## Bezel Diamond Pendants: 7 Reviews, Maximum Security Setting

[![Blue Nile pear bezel diamond pendant in 14K yellow gold lifestyle photo](/images/pendant-pear-bezel-yellow-gold-lifestyle.avif)](/images/pendant-pear-bezel-yellow-gold-lifestyle.avif)

The bezel setting wraps the diamond in a continuous rim of metal — the diamond is fully encased around its girdle with no exposed prongs. It is the most protective setting for everyday wear: nothing catches on fabric, nothing bends, and the diamond cannot rotate in the setting. The trade-off is slightly reduced light entry from the sides compared to a prong setting.

At Blue Nile, the round bezel pendants carry **7 verified reviews across all four carat weights**, no discount applied. These are full-price purchases confirmed by real buyers — a meaningful signal at $1,040–$7,460.

